%N A071943 Triangle T(n,k) (n>=0, 0 <= k <= n) read by rows giving number of underdiagonal lattice paths from (0,0) to (n,k) using only steps R=(1,0), V=(0,1) and D=(1,2).
%C A071943 For another interpretation of this array see the Example section.
%C A071943 Column k=2 is related to the triangular numbers: T(n,2) = A000217(n+1) - 3 for n>=2. Alternatively, T(n,2) = (n-1)*(n/2 + 2) for n >= 2. Coincidentally, it works for n=1 due to T(1,2) = 0, as defined in the formula below. - _Leonidas Liponis_, Dec 22 2025
%H A071943 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A071943/b071943.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..11475</a> (rows 0 <= n <= 150, flattened)
